People are being warned to keep their windows closed after a fire sent a column of smoke over Kent. A blaze has ripped through a building at Whitstable Harbour, gutting a retail premises. More than 40 firefighters are on the scene dealing with the incident. Several crews have been drafted in to bring the fire under control. The large business site overlooks the busy marina and is adjacent to a row of homes. Firefighters appear to have the blaze under control and have prevented it spreading to other properties. A suspected cause has not been publicly identified by the authorities. A Kent Fire and Rescue Service spokesman said: ‘Kent Fire and Rescue Service is at the scene of a fire at a commercial premises in Whitstable Harbour. ‘Eight fire engines and a height vehicle are in attendance and crews wearing breathing apparatus are working to extinguish the fire. ‘Crews are currently advising those who live or work in the area to keep windows and doors closed as a precaution due to smoke, and to avoid the area where possible while the emergency services deal with the incident.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.